The White House recently hosted a Women's Empowerment Panel, led by several women leaders in the Trump administration. President Donald Trump delivered remarks at the event, emphasizing the importance of enlisting the full potential of women in society. The administration has made it a priority to create an environment where women can thrive in the American economy. In February, President Trump and Prime Minister Trudeau launched the United States-Canada Council for Advancement of Women Entrepreneurs, and several events have been held to celebrate International Women's Day. The administration will continue to work towards ensuring that women can work and thrive in the American economy.